  "text": "Although the data integration problem taxonomy is very known, the growing tendency towards enterprise IT Architecture approaches brings new issues to the problem solution. An enterprise IT architecture is composed of a set of data and descriptive models that define the business, the information and the technology that support business operations, and keep them aligned with business goals (Lankhorst, 2005) . In this context, BPM may help in identifying data sources that need to be integrated,in keeping IT systems aligned with corporate strategic goals [CITATION_1] , and guiding service identification in a SOA implementation. SOA also contributes for interoperable and transparent solutions. In common scenarios where schema conflicts described above may involve both structured (e.g. a relational SGBD) and semi-structured data sources (XML files), service technology is advised.",
